                        "body":  "## Critical Issues Found - Blocking Merge\n\nThis PR contains fundamental logic errors in the test implementation that undermine the lock-free guarantees being tested:\n\n**Critical Defects:**\n1. **Struct Copy Semantics Bug** (Lines 30, 52): Tests modify struct copies instead of originals, invalidating state transition validation\n2. **Broken Atomic Operations** (Lines 199-211): `CompareExchange` on local variable instead of struct field, creating race conditions\n3. **Non-Atomic State Updates** (Line 209): Manual state assignment after failed atomic operation breaks thread safety\n\nThese defects cause tests to pass incorrectly while the actual concurrency guarantees fail. The PR cannot merge until these logic errors are fixed, as they compromise the entire test infrastructure\u0027s validity.\n\n---\nYou can now have the agent implement changes and create commits directly on your pull request\u0027s source branch. Simply comment with /q followed by your request in natural language to ask the agent to make changes.\n",
