o include\nthe V12 prefix per guidelines; change the class declaration from\nSIMADispatchBenchmark to a prefixed name like V12_001_SIMADispatchBenchmark or\nV12_002_SIMADispatchBenchmark (choose V12_001 for Panel or V12_002 for Strategy\nas appropriate), rename the file to match the new primary class name, and update\nall references (constructors, usages, test fixtures, and any registration code)\nto the new class identifier so the project compiles and follows the naming\nconvention.\n\nIn `@benchmarks/V12_Performance.Benchmarks.csproj`:\n- Around line 4-7: The project uses \u003cLangVersion\u003elatest\u003c/LangVersion\u003e, which\nmakes benchmark builds non-reproducible; update the LangVersion element to a\nfixed C# version compatible with net6.0 (for example \"10\" or \"10.0\") instead of\n\"latest\". Locate the LangVersion XML element in the same project file that\ncontains \u003cTargetFramework\u003enet6.0\u003c/TargetFramework\u003e and replace \"latest\" with the\nchosen numeric version to pin the language level for stable, reproducible\nbenchmark compilation.\n\nIn `@tests/V12_Performance.Tests/Core/FSMActorTests.cs`:\n- Line 98: The local variable initialState (declared as var initialState =\nactor.CurrentState;) is unused; remove that declaration to clean up the test (or\nif the original intent was to verify starting state, replace the unused variable\nwith an appropriate assertion against actor.CurrentState). Locate the\ndeclaration of initialState in the FSMActorTests test and either delete the line\nor convert it into an assertion that references actor.CurrentState.\n\nIn `@tests/V12_Performance.Tests/Core/OrderManagementTests.cs`:\n- Around line 194-214: CancelOrder is using Interlocked.CompareExchange on a\nlocal variable (currentState) instead of the actual stored state, so concurrent\ncancellations are not atomic; update OrderData to use an int backing field for\nits state (e.g., an internal/private int _state) and expose a method or property\nto map between OrderState and that int, then change CancelOrder to perform\nInterlocked.CompareExchange directly on that int field (e.g., ref data._state)\ncomparing Working -\u003e Cancelled and only set data.State (or return success) based\non the atomic result; alternatively add a TryCancelAtomic method on OrderData\nthat encapsulates the CAS logic and call that from CancelOrder.\n\nIn `@tests/V12_Performance.Tests/Mocks/INinjaTraderMocks.cs`:\n- Around line 1-3: Rename the file and its primary type to conform to the V12\nprefix convention: change the filename\ntests/V12_Performance.Tests/Mocks/INinjaTraderMocks.cs and the primary\ntype/interface INinjaTraderMocks to include the appropriate V12_001 (Panel) or\nV12_002 (Strategy) prefix (e.g., V12_001_INinjaTraderMocks or\nV12_002_INinjaTraderMocks) and update the namespace/type declarations\naccordingly; apply the same prefixing rule to the other affected declarations\nmentioned (lines covering the other types at 17-18, 30-31, 57-58, 69-70, 90-91,\n108-109, 118-119, 139-140, 148-149) so file names and primary classes/interfaces\nconsistently use V12_001 or V12_002 as required.\n\nIn `@tests/V12_Performance.Tests/V12_Performance.Tests.csproj`:\n- Around line 3-5: Update the V12_Performance.Tests project to target\nNinjaTrader 8 baseline by changing the \u003cTargetFramework\u003e from net6.0 to net48\nand set \u003cLangVersion\u003e to 8.0 (keep \u003cIsPackable\u003efalse as-is); edit the project\nfile entries for \u003cTargetFramework\u003e and \u003cLangVersion\u003e so the build/compiler use\n.NET Framework 4.8 and C# 8.0 instead of net6.0/latest.\n```\n\n\u003c/details\u003e\n\n\u003cdetails\u003e\n\u003csummary\u003eВӯЖ’В¬ГӨ Autofix (Beta)\u003c/summary\u003e\n\nFix all unresolved CodeRabbit comments on this PR:\n\n- [ ] \u003c!-- {\"checkboxId\": \"4b0d0e0a-96d7-4f10-b296-3a18ea78f0b9\"} --\u003e Push a commit to this branch (recommended)\n- [ ] \u003c!-- {\"checkboxId\": \"ff5b1114-7d8c-49e6-8ac1-43f82af23a33