u003csummary\u003eВӯЖ’Г¶Г§ Additional comments (7)\u003c/summary\u003e\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\n\u003cdetails\u003e\n\u003csummary\u003etests/V12_Performance.Tests/Mocks/INinjaTraderMocks.cs (1)\u003c/summary\u003e\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\n`30-37`: _ВӯЖ’Г…Г№ВҙВ©Г… Heavy lift_\n\n**Model mocks as immutable/value-safe to prevent invalid states by construction.**\n\nPublic setters permit unconstrained post-construction mutation (e.g., negative quantity/prices, inconsistent order snapshots). This violates the correctness-by-construction requirement.\n\n[ suggest_essential_refactor ] \n\u003cdetails\u003e\n\u003csummary\u003eProposed direction (pattern)\u003c/summary\u003e\n\n```diff\n-public struct MockOrder : IOrder\n+public readonly struct MockOrder : IOrder\n {\n-    public string Name { get; set; }\n-    public int Quantity { get; set; }\n-    public double LimitPrice { get; set; }\n-    public double StopPrice { get; set; }\n-    public OrderState OrderState { get; set; }\n+    public string Name { get; }\n+    public int Quantity { get; }\n+    public double LimitPrice { get; }\n+    public double StopPrice { get; }\n+    public OrderState OrderState { get; }\n\n     public MockOrder(string name, int quantity, double limitPrice, double stopPrice, OrderState state)\n     {\n         Name = name;\n         Quantity = quantity;\n         LimitPrice = limitPrice;\n         StopPrice = stopPrice;\n         OrderState = state;\n     }\n }\n```\n\u003c/details\u003e\n\nAs per coding guidelines, \"Correctness by Construction: Structure types, enums, and data models so it is mathematically impossible for the compiler to allow an invalid state; do not rely on runtime if/else guards for edge cases\".\n\n\nAlso applies to: 69-75, 118-123, 148-151\n\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\u003c/details\u003e\n\u003cdetails\u003e\n\u003csummary\u003etests/V12_Performance.Tests/Core/FSMActorTests.cs (2)\u003c/summary\u003e\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\n`1-14`: LGTM!\n\n\n\nAlso applies to: 15-29, 31-53, 55-82, 115-132\n\n---\n\n`135-186`: LGTM!\n\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\u003c/details\u003e\n\u003cdetails\u003e\n\u003csummary\u003etests/V12_Performance.Tests/Core/OrderManagementTests.cs (3)\u003c/summary\u003e\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\n`16-57`: LGTM!\n\n\n\nAlso applies to: 59-100, 129-150\n\n---\n\n`239-244`: LGTM!\n\n---\n\n`157-192`: LGTM!\n\n\n\nAlso applies to: 216-233\n\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\u003c/details\u003e\n\u003cdetails\u003e\n\u003csummary\u003ebenchmarks/Program.cs (1)\u003c/summary\u003e\u003cblockquote\u003e\n\n`15-15`: LGTM!\n\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\u003c/details\u003e\n\n\u003c/blockquote\u003e\u003c/details\u003e\n\n\u003c/details\u003e\n\n\u003c!-- This is an auto-generated comment by CodeRabbit for review status --\u003e",
